<kml xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/kml/2.2"><Document><name>Greece &amp; Italy 2026 — Trip Stops</name>
<Folder><name>Athens</name>
<Placemark><name>🏨 Anise Aluma Athens (Tapestry/Hilton)</name><description>Fri Jul 10 · Conf. #3471385009 — Evripidou 82. 2 rooms. 100k Hilton pts. Cancel by Jul 9.</description><Point><coordinates>23.7237,37.9805,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛰️ Areopagus (Mars Hill)</name><description>Fri Jul 10 · Free — ~15 min walk from the hotel. No ticket needed. Overlooks the Ancient Agora — birthplace of Stoicism (Stoa Poikile) and where Socrates held court. Sunset views of the Acropolis. Marble steps worn smooth — go slow.</description><Point><coordinates>23.7229,37.9719,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏛️ Acropolis Tour — Porinou 5</name><description>Sat Jul 11 · 7:50 AM · Tour Guy #1118765 — Meet at Porinou 5 (outside gates). $331.84, pay Jun 12.</description><Point><coordinates>23.7234,37.9714,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🎭 Open Air Ancient Greek Theatre</name><description>Sat Jul 11 · 9 PM · Tripadvisor #1778633837 — $143.76 charged Jul 9. No barcode — operator looks up by name.</description><Point><coordinates>23.7244,37.9693,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🥙 Athens Street Food Walk</name><description>Fri Jul 10 · 6:30 PM · Booking ref #1418536313 — Greekality (conf. 360081916). 4 adults. Meet at Syntagma Square by the round fountain. Souvlaki, peinirli, Greek doughnuts, koulouri. Ends at Monastiraki Square. Free cancellation before 6:30 PM EEST Jul 9.</description><Point><coordinates>23.7348,37.9756,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🚢 Piraeus Cruise Terminal</name><description>Sat Jul 11 · Board Viking OST — Limbers: #8663390 Stateroom 4071. Guernsey/Santi: #8663394 Stateroom 4073.</description><Point><coordinates>23.6359,37.9381,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
</Folder>
<Folder><name>Cruise</name>
<Placemark><name>🚢 Mykonos</name><description>Mon Jul 13 · 9:00 AM · $118/pp · Booked #1418529839 — Viator Mykonos Small Group Tour (not Viking, conf. VIA-96240517). Lighthouse, Ano Mera Monastery, Elia Beach, Old Town, Little Venice, Windmills. Substituted for Santorini due to weather. Pickup at Mykonos Cruise Ship Terminal, Tourlos.</description><Point><coordinates>25.3289,37.4467,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏟️ Katakolon / Olympia</name><description>Tue Jul 14 · Included — Ancient Olympia. 4 hours.</description><Point><coordinates>21.6317,37.6383,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏰 Corfu</name><description>Wed Jul 15 · Included — Panoramic Corfu &amp; Old Town.</description><Point><coordinates>19.9217,39.6243,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏰 Kotor, Montenegro</name><description>Thu Jul 16 · Included — Kotor on Foot. 1.5 hours.</description><Point><coordinates>18.7712,42.4247,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏰 Dubrovnik, Croatia</name><description>Fri Jul 17 · Included — Dubrovnik on Foot. 3 hours.</description><Point><coordinates>18.0944,42.6507,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🎵 Zadar — Sea Organ</name><description>Sat Jul 18 · Included — Walking Tour. Sea Organ + Sun Salutation.</description><Point><coordinates>15.2199,44.1172,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🦎 Postojna Cave, Slovenia</name><description>Sun Jul 19 · $199/pp — Postojna Cave &amp; Predjama Castle. 7.5 hours. 50°F inside.</description><Point><coordinates>14.2038,45.783,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
</Folder>
<Folder><name>Venice</name>
<Placemark><name>🏨 B&amp;B Ca' Bonvicini — Venice</name><description>Mon–Wed Jul 20–22 · Conf. #5062824483 — Santa Croce 2160. NON-REFUNDABLE. Check-in 9 AM–noon. Check-out 9–10 AM (very early!). No elevator. Canal view requested. +39 041 275 0106.</description><Point><coordinates>12.3302,45.4392,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🚗 Hertz — Venice Marco Polo Airport</name><description>Wed Jul 22 · 9:00 AM · Conf. #L60845394F2 — BMW X1 or similar. $855.85. Water taxi or ACTV Bus 5 from Venice (~20 min). Drop-off Rome FCO Aug 1, 7:30 AM.</description><Point><coordinates>12.3519,45.5054,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛵ Tour Guy Meeting — San Marco Columns</name><description>Tue Jul 21 · 8:45 AM · Tour Guy #1118847 — Between columns of San Marco and San Teodoro. $824.72, pay Jun 29.</description><Point><coordinates>12.3387,45.4341,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🔥 Murano — Glass-blowing</name><description>Tue Jul 21 · Afternoon · On tour — Live glass-blowing demonstration. 1,700°F molten silica.</description><Point><coordinates>12.3523,45.459,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🌈 Burano — Lacemaking</name><description>Tue Jul 21 · Afternoon · On tour — Colorful fishing village. Lacemaking demonstration + free time.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4167,45.4854,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
</Folder>
<Folder><name>Ferrara</name>
<Placemark><name>🏨 Casa D'Este - Hotel Ferrara</name><description>Wed–Thu Jul 22–23 · Conf. #5952657630 — Largo Castello 36. PIN 1176. 2 rooms (Joe &amp; Teri; Lorene &amp; Carla). Check-in from 3 PM (early arrival OK if room ready, otherwise free luggage storage). Breakfast included. Inside ZTL but check-in/out access permitted. Parking voucher €10/day at reception. +39 0532 205048. Cancel free until Jul 19.</description><Point><coordinates>11.6188,44.8386,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏰 Castello Estense</name><description>Wed Jul 22 · €12/pp (reduced €10) — Moated Renaissance castle in the city center. Dungeons, kitchens, frescoed apartments, and the Lions' Tower for rooftop views. Open daily ~9:30 AM–6 PM, last entry ~45 min before close. Plan 1.5 hours.</description><Point><coordinates>11.6198,44.8378,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ Ferrara Cathedral (San Giorgio)</name><description>Wed Jul 22 · Free — Basilica Cattedrale di San Giorgio, Piazza Duomo / Corso Martiri della Libertà 57. Reopened 2024 after restoration. Closes midday — open 8 AM–1 PM &amp; 4–8 PM.</description><Point><coordinates>11.6187,44.8364,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🕍 Jewish Ghetto — Via Mazzini</name><description>Wed Jul 22 · Free — Historic Jewish quarter since the 1600s: Via Mazzini, Via Vignatagliata, Via Vittoria. Synagogue on Via Mazzini in continuous use since the 15th century. Optional: MEIS museum, Via Piangipane 81 — Tue–Fri 10 AM–1 PM &amp; 3–5 PM, Sun 10 AM–6 PM, closed Sat &amp; Mon.</description><Point><coordinates>11.6213,44.8355,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
</Folder>
<Folder><name>Florence</name>
<Placemark><name>🏨 Loft Il Giobertino — Florence</name><description>Thu Jul 23–Fri Jul 24 · Conf. #5024697136 — Via Vincenzo Gioberti 95, 2nd floor. 1 two-bedroom apartment, all 4 guests. Check-in 3–10 PM. Check-out 6–10 AM. Kitchen + balcony. Cancel free until Jul 17.</description><Point><coordinates>11.2697,43.7736,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🔭 Galileo Museum</name><description>Thu Jul 23 · 11:30 AM · Booked, Order #53553 — Piazza dei Giudici 1. 4 tickets (reservation #s 211741–211744), €15 each. Time slot 11:30–12:30. Galileo's actual telescopes (discovered Jupiter's moons 1610), compass, orreries.</description><Point><coordinates>11.2559,43.7677,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>👑 Cappelle Medicee (Medici Chapel)</name><description>Thu Jul 23 · 4:00 PM · Booked, Order #23524226 — Piazza di Madonna degli Aldobrandini 6. 4 tickets (customer #4433426), €14 each. Time of entry 16:00–16:15. Michelangelo's New Sacristy: Night, Day, Dawn, Dusk.</description><Point><coordinates>11.2534,43.7751,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🔬 Da Vinci National Science Museum</name><description>Fri Jul 24 · Booked, Viator #1418564703 — Via Del Castellaccio 1R. Exchange voucher for direct entry ticket. Open 10 AM–6 PM. Italy's most important science museum. 170 Leonardo models + submarine + Moon fragment + spacecraft. 2+ hours.</description><Point><coordinates>11.2463,43.7638,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
</Folder>
<Folder><name>Tuscany</name>
<Placemark><name>🏨 Villa San Filippo — Chianti</name><description>Fri Jul 24–Sat Jul 25 · Conf. #72074703683732 — Strada delle Ginestre 6, Barberino Tavarnelle. $372.12. Check-in 2 PM. Pool, panoramic views, breakfast. ⚠️ CANCEL DEADLINE: JUL 10!</description><Point><coordinates>11.1673,43.5256,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ Badia a Passignano — Monastery</name><description>Possible stop · Fri Jul 24 — 11th-century Vallombrosan monastery. CLOSED TUESDAYS. Afternoon 3–5 PM.</description><Point><coordinates>11.2471,43.5773,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🍷 Greve in Chianti</name><description>Possible stop · Fri Jul 24 — Piazza Matteotti. Cantine Mirabilis walk-in wine tasting ~€1/pour.</description><Point><coordinates>11.3169,43.5825,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏘️ Barberino Tavarnelle</name><description>Fri Jul 24 · Afternoon — A charming comune in the Tuscan countryside, ~25 km south of Florence — one of "I Borghi più belli d'Italia" (the most beautiful villages in Italy). Villa San Filippo (tonight's hotel) is located here.</description><Point><coordinates>11.1794,43.5388,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🥩 Antica Macelleria Cecchini — Panzano</name><description>Dinner option A · Fri Jul 24 evening — Via XX Luglio 11, 50022 Panzano in Chianti. Dario Cecchini's legendary butcher-restaurant — theatrical owner, festive atmosphere, famous Costata alla Fiorentina T-bone. Also sells finocchiona salami. Open daily ~9 AM–4 PM (Fri/Sat to 6 PM). Book: Solociccia or Officina della Bistecca.</description><Point><coordinates>11.3163,43.5447,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🍷 Tenuta Torciano Cantina &amp; Ristorante</name><description>Dinner option B · Fri Jul 24 evening — Via Crocetta 18, Località Ulignano, San Gimignano. Family-owned winery since 1720 — cellar restaurant, tastings across Chianti Classico, Brunello, Vino Nobile, Vernaccia di San Gimignano. Also cooking classes, truffle hunts, helicopter rides. Open Mon–Fri 9 AM–11 PM, Sat–Sun 9:30 AM–midnight. torciano.com.</description><Point><coordinates>11.1315,43.463,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏘️ Radda in Chianti</name><description>Possible stop · Sat Jul 25 — Most "locals" of Chianti villages. Enoteca Bottega del Chianti Classico.</description><Point><coordinates>11.3747,43.4872,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏰 Castellina in Chianti</name><description>Possible stop — Medieval fortress. Underground Via delle Volte. Good lunch trattorias.</description><Point><coordinates>11.287,43.4691,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏰 Castello di Brolio</name><description>Sat Jul 25 · Crown jewel of route — €5 walk-in. Ramparts + gardens + enoteca. Ricasoli family since 1141. Open 10 AM–6 PM. Leave by 4:30 PM.</description><Point><coordinates>11.4635,43.4133,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏨 Idolina Guest House — Montalcino</name><description>Sat Jul 25–Sun Jul 26 · Conf. #72074700792366 — Via Mazzini 65/67. €262.62 at property. Check-in 1:30–7:30 PM. NO FRONT DESK — contact 24 hrs before.</description><Point><coordinates>11.4898,43.0602,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏰 Fortezza di Montalcino</name><description>Sat Jul 25 · Evening arrival ritual — €4 ramparts. Val d'Orcia views at golden hour. Brunello by the glass inside.</description><Point><coordinates>11.4891,43.0551,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏛️ Pienza</name><description>Sun Jul 26 · Optional — 30-min detour. Renaissance city. Famous pecorino cheese.</description><Point><coordinates>11.6784,43.0763,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ Sant'Antimo Abbey</name><description>Sun Jul 26 · En route — 12th-century Romanesque abbey. Gregorian chants.</description><Point><coordinates>11.476,42.9892,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
</Folder>
<Folder><name>Umbria</name>
<Placemark><name>🏨 Hotel Bellavista — Assisi</name><description>Sun–Tue Jul 26–28 · Conf. #6920407207 — Viale Patrono d'Italia 100. PIN 4429. 1st floor, no elevator. Breakfast 8–9:30 AM. Restaurant closed Thursdays. Payment at restaurant. Pool 9 AM–7 PM. €410.24 auto-charged Jul 19.</description><Point><coordinates>12.5934,43.065,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ Basilica of St. Francis — Mass + Vespers</name><description>Sun Jul 26 · 5 PM Italian Mass + Vespers — 800th anniversary year. Book "Participation" at sanfrancescoassisi.org.</description><Point><coordinates>12.6054,43.075,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🌲 Eremo delle Carceri</name><description>Mon Jul 27 · Afternoon — St. Francis's hermitage 4 km above Assisi. Free. Deeply quiet.</description><Point><coordinates>12.6519,43.0631,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🎨 Santa Maria Maggiore — Spello</name><description>Tue Jul 28 · Morning — Pinturicchio frescoes. Almost always empty. 15 min from Assisi.</description><Point><coordinates>12.6719,42.9898,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏨 Hotel Duomo — Orvieto</name><description>Tue–Wed Jul 28–29 · Conf. #72074704255117 — Vicolo di Maurizio 7. Steps from Duomo. $407.72. Check-in 2–10 PM. Cancel free until Jul 26.</description><Point><coordinates>12.113,42.7176,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ Orvieto Cathedral + Underground</name><description>Tue Jul 28 · Afternoon — Gothic facade. Signorelli frescoes. Orvieto Underground (~€6/pp, orvietounderground.it).</description><Point><coordinates>12.1133,42.7171,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
</Folder>
<Folder><name>Rome</name>
<Placemark><name>🏨 Rome Hotel (TBD)</name><description>Wed–Fri Jul 29–31 · 3 nights — Must confirm parking ~€25–35/night. Bonvoy: The Regency Rome. Hilton: Aleph Rome Hotel Curio (★4.6) or DoubleTree Rome Monti.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4964,41.9028,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🕯️ Vatican Scavi / Necropolis</name><description>Wed Jul 29 · Afternoon · BOOK NOW — Only 250/day. 90-min small group. St. Peter's tomb. Must finish by ~4 PM for cooking class.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4539,41.9016,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏛️ Pantheon</name><description>Book pantheonroma.com · ~€5/pp — World's largest unreinforced concrete dome. Book in advance.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4769,41.8986,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🕍 Vatican Museums — Meeting Point</name><description>Thu Jul 30 · 7:15 AM · Tour Guy #1123725 — Under Michelangelo and Raphael statues. $721.16, pay Jul 8. Walks Inside Rome. Max 10.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4536,41.9065,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ St. Peter's Basilica</name><description>Thu Jul 30 · Via Scala Regia — Scala Regia exclusive to guided groups. Free time: Pietà, baldachin, Vatican Grottoes.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4539,41.9022,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏟️ Colosseum — Metro Stop</name><description>Fri Jul 31 · 8:45 AM · Tour Guy #1117159 — $1,018.70, pay Jul 3 (EARLIEST). Private tour with Arena Floor. No large backpacks. ID required.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4922,41.8902,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>🏛️ Roman Forum + Palatine Hill</name><description>Fri Jul 31 · On Colosseum tour — Included. 2,500 years of history in one walk.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4864,41.8921,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ Basilica of San Clemente (Alternate)</name><description>Teresa researched · Near Colosseum — Three underground layers: 12th-century basilica → 4th-century church → 1st-century Mithraic temple. Most extraordinary Catholic site most tourists miss.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4966,41.8895,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ Scala Sancta (Alternate)</name><description>Teresa researched — The Holy Stairs. Pilgrims ascend on knees. Next to San Giovanni Laterano.</description><Point><coordinates>12.5089,41.8858,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ San Giovanni Laterano (Alternate)</name><description>Teresa researched — Rome's actual cathedral — outranks St. Peter's ecclesiastically. Far fewer tourists.</description><Point><coordinates>12.5054,41.8859,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ Santa Maria sopra Minerva (Alternate)</name><description>Teresa researched · 2 min from Pantheon — St. Catherine of Siena's tomb. Rome's only Gothic church. Almost no queue.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4772,41.8983,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ Catacombs of Priscilla (Alternate)</name><description>Teresa researched · Closed Mondays — "Queen of the Catacombs." 7+ miles of tunnels. Oldest image of the Virgin Mary (~3rd century). Book at catacombepriscilla.com.</description><Point><coordinates>12.5115,41.9302,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>⛪ Capuchin Crypt (Alternate)</name><description>Teresa researched — Bones of 4,000 Capuchin friars arranged as art. Powerful memento mori. 45 min.</description><Point><coordinates>12.4883,41.9059,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>✈️ Fiumicino Airport (FCO)</name><description>Sat Aug 1 · Hertz drop-off 7:30 AM · Fly home IAD — ~35–45 min drive from central Rome. Return Hertz BMW X1 (Conf. #L60845394F2). Allow 3 hours before departure.</description><Point><coordinates>12.2519,41.8034,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
</Folder>
